comment.text: This translation key is used to display a button label that triggers setting up a development environment. It appears in a small navigation button on a Portal Settings page, prompting users to start the setup process.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Greek translation "Έναρξη ρύθμισης" while literally meaning 'Start of configuration/adjustment,' doesn't quite capture the nuance of 'Start setting up'. It sounds a bit formal and technical for the implied context of a Javascript SDK. A more natural phrasing would convey a sense of initiation or beginning the setup process.

While "Commencer le réglage" is understandable, a more idiomatic and accurate translation of "Start setting up" would be "Démarrer la configuration" or "Lancer la configuration". "Réglage" often implies adjustment rather than initial setup.

While "設定開始" (settei kaishi) is understandable, a more natural and accurate translation of "Start setting up" would be something like "設定を開始する" (settei o kaishi suru) or "セットアップを開始する" (settapu o kaishi suru). "設定開始" feels abrupt and less idiomatic.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: 設定を開始する (settei o kaishi suru) or セットアップを開始する (settapu o kaishi suru)

ai_spell_check_issues.description: While "설정 시작" is understandable, a more natural and accurate translation of "Start setting up" would be "설정 시작하기" or "설정하기 시작".  "설정 시작" feels slightly abrupt and doesn't fully convey the ongoing action implied by "Start setting up".

The translation "Setare Start" is not a natural or accurate translation of "Start setting up." "Setare" means 'setting' or 'configuration,' and 'Start' is just 'Start.' This doesn't convey the meaning of initiating a setup process.
The translation uses two separate words instead of a single phrase. A more fluid translation would improve readability.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: A more integrated phrase would be better than two separate words.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Sinhala translation 'ආරම්භය පිහිටුවමින්' doesn't accurately convey the meaning of 'Start setting up'. 'ආරම්භය' means 'beginning' or 'start', and 'පහිටුවමින්' suggests 'installing' or 'establishing'. The translation focuses on the process of establishing, rather than the action of starting the setup.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider a more direct translation like 'පිහිටුවීම ආරම්භ කරන්න' (pihita uvima arambakara naa) which means 'Start the setup' or 'ආරම්භ කිරීම' (arambha karama) which means 'to begin'.
